race.description: Victor Harbor Motor Co Maiden Plate
race.comment: AUSTRALIA FOREVER (12) closed off strongly last start to get up for second, beaten a neck, over 1350m at this track on debut. Can go one better with that run under her belt. IMPENDING FURY (8) improved nicely in his second start when battling on gamely into fourth. Strips fitter and keeps Holder. Have to take seriously. IMPACT STORM (7) finished alongside IMPENDING FURY on debut at the latest. Should appreciate the extra ground and is among the better hopes. MOUSSAKA (5) was well supported in town at the latest but could only manage fifth. Peak fitness now, so is worth following up but he will need a smart steer from the wide alley. MIDLIFE CRISIS (4) was much better last start at Oakbank when in the placings. Blinkers going on will have him focused. No reason he can't land the winning blow.
